 will be in front of Marshall Museum    Shuttle services will be provided from VMI Post locations to Cameron Hall from 7 a m  until 4 p m  In the event that the Parade Ground is closed for parking due to inclement weather  shuttle services will be provided from the Lowe s parking lot    An information table with brochures will be set up in front of Preston Library  Unloading Baggage Please use extreme caution during this period  You must unload baggage by 1 30 p m  Please note that room assignments will be provided at matriculation processing in Cameron Hall  Due to congestion in front of Barracks  we suggest that new cadets carry their luggage to Barracks from the Parade Ground parking area if possible  If you desire to move your vehicle in front of the Barracks to unload  please follow these procedures  1  Exit the Parade Ground parking area at the designated spot and travel around the Parade Ground in a counter clockwise direction VMI officials will direct you where to stop your vehicle to unload  2    The area in front of Barracks is for unloading only  Unload all of your cadet s baggage where directed  The driver must stay with the vehicle   Airport style drop off  3    Immediately after your vehicle is unloaded  proceed through the semi circle and continue back to the Parade Ground parking area  4    Park the vehicle and rejoin your cadet  Lunch Lunch will be provided for the new cadets from 11 00 a m    1 30 p m  in Crozet Hall  New cadets can eat at no charge  the cost for family members for lunch is 9 00  includes tax  for adults and children  children 5 and under eat free It is important that new cadets eat during this time and to drink plenty of fluids with the meal  Dress Be sure to wear casual clothing and good walking shoes  The weather in August tends to be hot and humid and we want you to be as comfortable as possible  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 